===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|beginnen}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|beginnan||to begin}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*biginnaną||to begin}} (compare West Frisian {{m|fy|begjinne}}, {{cog|nds|begünnen}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} and {{etyl|de|-}} {{m|nl|beginnen}}), from a root *''ginnaną'' also found in Old English {{m|ang|onginnan}}, Old Saxon {{m|osx|andginnan}} and Dutch {{m|nl|ontginnen}}, possibly from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*gʰed-||to take}} (compare {{cog|cy|genni||to delve, submerge oneself}}, {{cog|la|prehendō||to grasp, nab}}, {{cog|sq|zë||to catch}}, {{cog|grc|χανδάνω||to hold, contain}}).

